    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Asterisk for Jones?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Matthew Duda letter discusses Tiger Woods margin of victory at United States Open at Pebble Beach (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Clifton Brown correctly reports the official United States Golf Association statistic that Tiger Woods's victory at Pebble Beach was by far the largest margin in history (15 shots). However, surely Bobby Jones's feat in the 1929 United States Open deserves at least an asterisk. In that 36-hole playoff, Jones beat Al Espinoza by an amazing 23 strokes.</p>
        <p>MATTHEW DUDA  Los Angeles</p>
      </block>
